Product recalls are issued because of safety or quality concerns in the manufacturing of a product. Food recalls are issued when a product is unsafe to eat, due to contamination or misbranding. While they are rarely issued, they should be taken seriously. Below is the list of items recalled at supermarkets Tesco, Morrisons John Lewis and Lidl. Trewithen Dairy Unsalted Butter 250g This product has been recalled because it contains a high level of E. coli. The best before date is May 23, 2022. The batch code is G2 073. Tesco stated: “If you’ve bought an affected product, please don’t eat it. Instead, return it to a Tesco store where a full refund will be given. No receipt is required.” READ MORE: Michael Mosley's secret ingredient for healthy chocolate brownies  Morrisons Elements Scented Candles This product has been recalled because there is a risk that some candles may burn in an uncontrolled manner presenting a fire risk. Morrisons stated: “If you have purchased one of these candles, do not burn it and return it to your nearest Morrisons store for a full refund. We don't need a receipt.” They added: “No other candles are affected by this recall.” The candle is available in four variants: Fire, Water, Earth and Air. Morrisons have recalled a selection of Snaffling Pig products due to the presence of salmonella. Snaffling Pig Porky Puffs Low & Slow BBQ Pack size: All All dates up to and including June 25, 2022 Snaffling Pig Salt and Black Pepper Pack size: All Best before: All dates up to and including September 23, 2022 Snaffling Pig Pork Scratchings Perfectly Salted Pack size: All Best before: All dates up to and including June 25, 2022 Snaffling Pig Porky Puffs Marvellous Maple Pack size: All Best before: All dates up to and including June 25, 2022 Awfully Posh Pork Puff Original Pack size: All Best before: All dates up to and including June 25, 2022 Awfully Posh Pork Puff Honey BBQ Pack size: All Best before: All dates up to and including June 25, 2022 Awfully Posh Pork Scratchings Traditional Pack size: All Best before: All dates up to and including June 25, 2022 Awfully Posh Pork Crackling Chili & Garlic Pack size: All Best before: All dates up to and including July 23, 2022 Awfully Posh Pork Crackling Sea Salt Pack size: All Best before: All dates up to and including July 23, 2022. Morrisons said: “Freshers Foods Ltd are recalling a range of products due to the presence of Salmonella, and also taking the precautionary step of recalling other lines due to the risk of Salmonella. “If you have purchased this product, please do not eat it. Instead, return it to the store you purchased it from for a full refund.” John Lewis has also recalled some food products by Snaffling Pig due to the presence of salmonella. Pigs in Blanket Glass 1.5l Jar (77067505) Snaffling Pig 1.5l Jar BBQ (77067503) Snaffling Pig 1.5l Jar Black Pepper (77067502) Sweet n Bold Pig N’ Mix (77067506) Pork Scratching Advent (78435404) Snaffling Pig Beer and Advent 2021 Calendar (78435403) Snaffling Pig Marvellous Maple 1.5l jar (78066801) Snaffling Pig Salt and Vinegar 1.5l jar (78066802) Snaffling Pig Thai Sweet Chilli 1.5l glass jar (77067509) John Lewis & Partners Beer Crate Hamper (54631314) John Lewis & Partners Wayfarer Hamper (54631704). All products have a best before date of September 23, 2022. John Lewis warned: “The Snaffling Pig Co is recalling the below products as a precautionary measure due to the potential presence of Salmonella, which may lead to illness if consumed.” Lidl Northern Ireland has recalled Culinea Paella due to allergens not discussed in English. It contains crustaceans, fish, milk and molluscs which are not mentioned in English on the label. The pack size is 750g. The batch code is L1354-2. The best before date is June 23, 2023. Lidl stated: “If you have bought the above product and have an allergy or intolerance to the allergens, we advise you not to consume it. “Instead, return the product to a Lidl store for a full refund, with or without a receipt.”